values:
ok so I'm at work. Its way too early to be awake and I have to sit here for 8 hours...hopefully less if I can convince James that I should leave earlier.&nbsp;

Carly and Peter got here last night and we unloaded my car which was full of stuff and moved my bed into my apartment. Then we went to dinner with Kagun and then back to his apartment to sleep. I didn't get to bed until about two...which sucks when you have to be at work by 8 and you were exhausted when you finally did go to sleep.

Today, I'm hoping to finish moving everything, maybe start cleaning the room and then go to sleep so that tomorrow we can finish cleaning and then go shopping for the rest of the things I need for my apartment :) Unfortunately, Kagun has dance tonight so he can't help me move but him letting us crash at his apartment is wonderful of him. He makes me so happy.&nbsp;

The RAs are all at breakfast and the football players are either at practice or asleep, so I really have no point in working the front desk. I think James is going to have me do things later but other than that I have to just sit here and worry about haveing 25 hours after work to get everything out and to make the room sparkle.&nbsp;

I'll be home at the end of the week...so we need to have a get together and do something to celebrate the end of summer. Granted for me its the only summer I've had. I've been working and going to school all summer.

Well that's about it for now. I'll keep everyone posted and I'll take pictures of my apartment when I'm fully moved in and when I'm technically allowed to move in since that isn't until wednesday.

Hearts, Stars, and Shamrocks,
Kim

Just found out that no one is coming in at midnight...meaning I need to work until 4am....however I htink I may have found a way to get it covered so that I can sleep.&nbsp;

Currently my back is killing me, though the stomach pain has disappeared and thank goodness for that.&nbsp;

I'm wanting to write a lot lately, but have not had the inspiration for the correct themes or diction. I got a really awesome notebook at the store today, although I really don't need anymore notebooks to write in.

Things are going okay. I need to find boxes...badly, I need to start packing. I need to study for my finals. Most of all, I need to relax because my mother may be right in that the pain in my stomach could be the start of an olsar* Yay me. Right?!

Anywho, I guess that'll be about all for tonight. I'll probably update tomorrow when I work again as it seems to be the only time I really sit down bored at the computer anymore.

